description:
I ate my way through Korean traditional markets only eating the best korean street food in Seoul. I went to shinchang market located in north east of seoul and gwangjang market. I recommend you go check out shinchang market when you're in Seoul because it's not crowded and you'll be able to get a taste for local street delights. Gwangjang market is also definitely a place you need to go visit, but the real tip is to go later at night to avoid the crowds and enjoy the ~real vibes~

Here are the list of places I went to 
📍신창시장 Shinchang Sijang
서울 도봉구 창2동 창2동 581

📍 씨앗호떡 Ssiat Hotteuk 
서울 도봉구 덕릉로 238 명금당

📍 신창튀김 Sinchang Tweegim 
(Walk inside the market and on your right)

📍소문난 순대국 Somoonnan Soondaegook
574-28 Dobong-dong, Dobong-gu, Seoul

📍창동 할머니 토스트 Changdong Halmoni Toast 
15 Deongneung-ro 60da-gil, Dobong-gu, Seoul

📍신송 분식 Shinsong Bunsik
Seoul, Dobong-gu, 창제2동 581-75 1층

📍Gyeran Bbang / Corn / Sweet Potato 
(Walk further inside the market on your left)

📍대전곱창 Daejun Gopchang
서울 종로구 종로38길 8

📍Buchon Yukhoe
200-12 종로, Jongno-gu, Seoul

📍해동이네 
138-31 종로5.6가동 Jongno-gu, Seoul
OR East Cart #42 Haedong's inside Gwangjang Market 

📍광장시장 찹쌀꽈배기 
Seoul, Jongno-gu, Jongno 4(sa)-ga, 188 105호
